<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,818,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,854,880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[454,547,854,880]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Thespea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[454,547,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Thespea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished on the basis of: i) in both sexes, usually green forewings with marginal series of small brown spots, ii) in the male genitalia, the valva is generally distally divided into saccular (valvula) and costal processes (cucullus) and iii) vesica with a long row of claw-like or saw shaped cornutus (
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyev, A. V." pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref6038" refString="Solovyev, A. V. (2014) Parasa Moore auct.: phylogenetic review of the complex from the Palaearctic and Indomalayan regions (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae). Proceedings of the Museum Witt, Munich, 1, 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="2014">Solovyev 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,818,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,409,998,1024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[545,638,998,1024]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Thespea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[545,638,998,1024]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Thespea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Oriental genus and many of its species are externally similar to the members of 
<emphasis box="[334,415,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Soteira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyev, A. V." box="[423,600,1034,1060]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref6038" refString="Solovyev, A. V. (2014) Parasa Moore auct.: phylogenetic review of the complex from the Palaearctic and Indomalayan regions (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae). Proceedings of the Museum Witt, Munich, 1, 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="2014">Solovyev, 2014</bibRefCitation>
, although smaller in size, and antenna shows longer rami basally. Another similar genus is 
<emphasis box="[332,429,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Circeida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Solovyev, A. V." box="[436,612,1070,1096]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="1 - 240" refId="ref6038" refString="Solovyev, A. V. (2014) Parasa Moore auct.: phylogenetic review of the complex from the Palaearctic and Indomalayan regions (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae). Proceedings of the Museum Witt, Munich, 1, 1 - 240." type="journal article" year="2014">Solovyev, 2014</bibRefCitation>
, but the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[777,870,1070,1096]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Thespea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[777,870,1070,1096]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Thespea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable by the male genitalia: i) absence of anellus processes (in 
<emphasis box="[419,516,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Circeida</emphasis>
the anellus bears a pair of strongly sclerotized naked spurs), ii) vesica with typical saw shaped cornutus and iii) valva with distal saccular process (in 
<emphasis box="[915,1012,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Circeida</emphasis>
vesica is without cornutus and distal saccular process). With the new species we describe here, the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1005,1178,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Thespea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[912,1005,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Thespea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by 26 species, with five species and one subspecies recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[623,681,1214,1240]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">India</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authority="bicolor (Walker, 1855)" authorityName="bicolor (Walker" authorityYear="1855" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[696,1067,1214,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Neaera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bicolor" subSpecies="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[696,891,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">T. bicolor bicolor</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[905,1059,1214,1241]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" refId="ref6113" refString="Walker, F. (1855) s. n. In: List of the specimens of Lepidopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Vol. 5. Trustees of the British Museum, London, pp. 977 - 1258." type="book" year="1855">Walker, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
